---
mode: prompt
model: anthropic:claude-sonnet
tools:
  - read_file
  - search
---
# H7a — terminal integration-acceptance fixture.
#
# A single representative multi-feature `.loom` whose composed pipeline path the
# H7a integration-acceptance gate drives end-to-end through the H4a harness:
# typed query -> tool loop -> code-tool invoke -> schema lowering/validation ->
# binder -> cancellation, in one run against the in-process Pi session double.
#
# The composed observable transcript this fixture produces is enumerated in
# `golden-transcript.json`; the `loom-system-note` codes its path emits are
# enumerated in `golden-diagnostics.json`; the manually-maintained best-effort
# union of every code the Deps slices *can* emit is in `permitted-codes.json`.

schema Report {
  status: "ok" | "degraded"
  summary: string
}

# Free-phase tool loop: the model inspects the workspace with a parallel
# `read_file` / `search` batch (a mixed-success code-tool invoke, V14a/V14b),
# then a terminating turn. The binder resolves the model via a transport-class
# retry then success (V11a/V11f). The typed `@`-query lowers its response
# against `Report` (V5d/V13b) and forces a two-phase respond turn (V13c/V13d).
let report: Report = @`Inspect the workspace and report its configuration.`

respond report
